# Agoge Design System

## Color palette (CSS variables in `frontend/src/index.css`)

| Variable | Hex | Use |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `--black` | `#000000` | Main site background |
| `--bone` | `#E3DED4` | Headlines, primary text |
| `--gold` | `#A88147` | Primary brand: borders, buttons, accents |
| `--bronze` | `#795E36` | Hover states, dividers, secondary accents |
| `--red` | `#801C10` | Alerts, highlights, CTA accents (use sparingly) |
| `--brown` | `#3B2A1C` | Cards, panels, subtle backgrounds |
| `--gray` | `#B3ACA1` | Secondary text |

Derived shades: `--brown-dark` (#241a11), `--near-black` (#0c0906).
ALWAYS use the CSS variables, never hard-code hex values in component CSS.

## Typography

- Display/headings: `var(--font-display)` — Barlow Condensed (900 for titles, uppercase)
- Body: `var(--font-body)` — Barlow (300/400 weights)
- Loaded via Google Fonts in `frontend/index.html`

## Brand motif

The Greek letter Λ (lambda, Spartan shield symbol) in gold is the brand mark —
used in section labels (`.section-label::before`), list bullets, nav, and footer.

## Conventions

- Each section component has a co-located `.css` file it imports.
- Shared classes from `index.css`: `.btn-primary`, `.btn-outline`, `.section-label`,
  `.section-title`, `.section-note`, `.texture-overlay`, `.form-group`, `.form-row`.
- Sections: full-width, `padding: 100px 4%`, inner wrapper `max-width: 1150px`.
- Responsive breakpoints: 960px (primary), 720px/480px where needed.
